HEADWORD: Pulmograde
<hw>Pul"mo*grade</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>pulmo</ets> a lung + <ets>gradi</ets> to walk.]</ety>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Swimming by the expansion and contraction, or
lunglike movement, of the body, or of the disk, as do the
medus⟦ae⟧.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

